^RC(343,18,1,1,0)="This is additional information for you about the possible referral of"
^RC(343,18,1,2,0)="debts to the Department of Treasury."
^RC(343,18,1,3,0)=" "
^RC(343,18,1,4,0)="If we do not hear from you, we will report your debt to the U.S."
^RC(343,18,1,5,0)="Department of the Treasury for cross-servicing and/or the Treasury Offset"
^RC(343,18,1,6,0)="Program (TOP).  Additionally, you will be responsible for any and all fees"
^RC(343,18,1,7,0)="associated with cross servicing and the offset program."
^RC(343,18,1,8,0)=" "
^RC(343,18,1,9,0)="Once your debt is submitted for cross-servicing, the U.S. Department of"
^RC(343,18,1,10,0)="Treasury may refer your debt to a private collection agency for collection"
^RC(343,18,1,11,0)="action, report your debt to a credit bureau and if the debt is written"
^RC(343,18,1,12,0)="off, report it to IRS as potential taxable income."
^RC(343,18,1,13,0)=" "
^RC(343,18,1,14,0)="If your debt is submitted to the TOP, the U.S. Department of Treasury will"
^RC(343,18,1,15,0)="reduce or withhold any of your eligible Federal payments by the amount of"
^RC(343,18,1,16,0)="your debt.  The Debt Collection Act of 1982 and the Debt Collection"
^RC(343,18,1,17,0)="Improvement Act of 1996 authorize this process, known as offset.  Federal"
^RC(343,18,1,18,0)="payments eligible for offset include:"
^RC(343,18,1,19,0)="        .  Your income tax refunds"
^RC(343,18,1,20,0)="        .  Your Federal salary pay, including military pay"
^RC(343,18,1,21,0)="        .  Your Federal retirement, including military retirement pay"
^RC(343,18,1,22,0)="        .  Your contractor/vendor payments"
^RC(343,18,1,23,0)="        .  Certain Federal benefit payments, such as Social Security"
^RC(343,18,1,24,0)="           (other than Supplemental Security Income (SSI)), Railroad"
^RC(343,18,1,25,0)="           Retirement (other than tier 2), and Black Lung (part B)"
^RC(343,18,1,26,0)="           benefits"
^RC(343,18,1,27,0)="        .  Other Federal payments, including certain loans to you, that"
^RC(343,18,1,28,0)="           are not exempt from offset"
^RC(343,18,1,29,0)=" "
^RC(343,18,1,30,0)="If you have filed for bankruptcy and the automatic stay is in effect, you"
^RC(343,18,1,31,0)="must notify us within 30 days to prevent this debt from being reported to"
^RC(343,18,1,32,0)="the Treasury Department.  You should send us proof of your bankruptcy.  If"
^RC(343,18,1,33,0)="you file a joint federal income tax return, you should obtain IRS Form"
^RC(343,18,1,34,0)="8379, Injured Spouse Claim and Allocation, BEFORE filing your return.  The"
^RC(343,18,1,35,0)="instructions will explain the steps your spouse may take to obtain his/her"
^RC(343,18,1,36,0)="share of your joint income tax refund."
^RC(343,18,1,37,0)=" "
^RC(343,18,1,38,0)="If you are or become a Federal Employee, your current net disposable pay"
^RC(343,18,1,39,0)="is subject to offset if you do not pay your debt or take other action as"
^RC(343,18,1,40,0)="described on the previous page.  Under the TOP, the U.S. Treasury will"
^RC(343,18,1,41,0)="deduct up to 15% of your disposable pay, beginning in the pay period that"
^RC(343,18,1,42,0)="your debt is submitted to the TOP.  This deduction will continue every pay"
^RC(343,18,1,43,0)="period until your debt, including interest, penalties and other costs, is"
^RC(343,18,1,44,0)="paid in full."
^RC(343,18,1,45,0)=" "
^RC(343,18,1,46,0)="You are entitled to a hearing to dispute the amount of the payroll"
^RC(343,18,1,47,0)="deduction.  To request a hearing, you must file a written request for a"
^RC(343,18,1,48,0)="hearing no later than 15 days from the date of this letter to prevent"
^RC(343,18,1,49,0)="referral of your debt to the Treasury Department."
^RC(343,18,2)="Treasury letter to be attached to 3rd demand letter"
^RC(343,19,0)="BENEFICIARY TRAVEL NOTICE"
^RC(343,19,1,0)="S ^343.01^135^135^3161121^S ^S ^S ^"
^RC(343,19,1,1,0)="|TOP|NOTICE OF RIGHTS AND RESPONSIBILITIES"
^RC(343,19,1,2,0)="__________________________________________________________________________     "
^RC(343,19,1,3,0)="COLLECTION:  The U.S. Department of Veterans Affairs (VA) is required to       "
^RC(343,19,1,4,0)="collect debts owed to the government.  Action must be taken within sixty       "
^RC(343,19,1,5,0)="(60) days from the initial billing statement to pay your debt in full or       "
^RC(343,19,1,6,0)="establish a payment plan or your account may be referred for further           "
^RC(343,19,1,7,0)="collection action.  You have the right to inspect and copy the records         "
^RC(343,19,1,8,0)="related to the debt.  You also have the right to establish a payment plan.     "
^RC(343,19,1,9,0)="You have the right to submit a compromise offer.  You have the right to        "
^RC(343,19,1,10,0)="request a waiver and a hearing on the waiver request.  Collection action      "
^RC(343,19,1,11,0)="includes referring your delinquent balance to the Department of               "
^RC(343,19,1,12,0)="Treasury's Treasury Offset Program, which will include offset of any          "
^RC(343,19,1,13,0)="federal and state payments to which you are entitled.  This includes tax      "
^RC(343,19,1,14,0)="refunds, social security benefits and salary or retirement benefits.          "
^RC(343,19,1,15,0)="_________________________________________________________________________     "
^RC(343,19,1,16,0)="PAY YOUR BILL:  Pay the debt in full by the balance due date on the"
^RC(343,19,1,17,0)="initial billing statement to avoid late charges and collection action:"
^RC(343,19,1,18,0)="    In Person: At your local Veteran Affairs Medical Center's Agent"
^RC(343,19,1,19,0)="               Cashier's Office"
^RC(343,19,1,20,0)="    By Phone:  (see below for local information)"
^RC(343,19,1,21,0)="    By Mail:   (see below for local information)"
^RC(343,19,1,22,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,23,0)="LATE CHARGES:  The VA is required to assess late charges on balances which"
^RC(343,19,1,24,0)="remain unpaid thirty (30) days after the statement date.  These charges"
^RC(343,19,1,25,0)="consist of interest and administrative fees at rates established each"
^RC(343,19,1,26,0)="year.  Interest will be charged from the date charges first appear on the"
^RC(343,19,1,27,0)="statement. You can avoid these charges by making timely payments by the"
^RC(343,19,1,28,0)="balance due date on the statement.  A monthly administrative cost or"
^RC(343,19,1,29,0)="collection fee will be added to your debt if, within thirty (30) days of"
^RC(343,19,1,30,0)="the date of the statement on which charges first appear, full payment of"
^RC(343,19,1,31,0)="the debt is not received or a repayment plan agreement is not approved."
^RC(343,19,1,32,0)="If an installment repayment plan is established and any installment is not"
^RC(343,19,1,33,0)="received by the due date, the monthly administrative cost or collection"
^RC(343,19,1,34,0)="fee will thereafter be charged until the debt is paid.  Other collection"
^RC(343,19,1,35,0)="costs may be added to the debt if additional collection actions become "
^RC(343,19,1,36,0)="necessary."
^RC(343,19,1,37,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,38,0)="WAIVER:  You have the right to request a waiver of part or all of your"
^RC(343,19,1,39,0)="debt.  If the waiver is granted you will not be required to pay the amount"
^RC(343,19,1,40,0)="waived.  To do so, submit an explanation and a completed Financial Status"
^RC(343,19,1,41,0)="Report (VA Form 5655) found at:  www.domain.ext/vaforms/va/pdf/VA5655.pdf."
^RC(343,19,1,42,0)="Your explanation should include why you are not responsible for the debt"
^RC(343,19,1,43,0)="and any undue hardship the payment of the debt would cause you.  You have"
^RC(343,19,1,44,0)="the right to request a hearing in connection with your request for a"
^RC(343,19,1,45,0)="waiver.  To do so, submit a written request for hearing with your waiver"
^RC(343,19,1,46,0)="request.  VA will notify you of the date, time and place where the hearing"
^RC(343,19,1,47,0)="will be held.  Refer to the ""Customer Service"" and ""Submitting Your"
^RC(343,19,1,48,0)="Request"" sections below for more information."
^RC(343,19,1,49,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,50,0)="COMPROMISE OFFER:  You have the right to request a compromise.  A"
^RC(343,19,1,51,0)="compromise means you may propose a lesser amount as full settlement of the"
^RC(343,19,1,52,0)="debt.  To request a compromise, submit your request in writing to VA,"
^RC(343,19,1,53,0)="specifying the dollar amount you are proposing VA should accept as payment"
^RC(343,19,1,54,0)="in full, and a completed Financial Status Report (VA Form 5655) found at:"
^RC(343,19,1,55,0)="www.domain.ext/vaforms/va/pdf/VA5655.pdf.  Refer to the ""Customer Service"""
^RC(343,19,1,56,0)="and ""Submitting Your Request"" sections below for more information."
^RC(343,19,1,57,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,58,0)="REPAYMENT PLAN:  You have the right to establish a monthly repayment plan"
^RC(343,19,1,59,0)="at any time during your enrollment in VA health care if you cannot pay"
^RC(343,19,1,60,0)="your debt in full.  To do so, submit a completed Agreement to Pay"
^RC(343,19,1,61,0)="Indebtedness (VA Form 1100) found at:"
^RC(343,19,1,62,0)="www.domain.ext/vaforms/va/pdf/VA1100.pdf.  Indicate your proposed monthly"
^RC(343,19,1,63,0)="payment amount in paragraph 1A.  Refer to the ""Customer Service"" and"
^RC(343,19,1,64,0)="""Submitting Your Request"" sections below for more information."
^RC(343,19,1,65,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,66,0)="DISPUTE THE EXISTENCE OR AMOUNT OF THE DEBT:  You have the right to"
^RC(343,19,1,67,0)="dispute the existence or amount of the debt.  To do so, submit a letter"
^RC(343,19,1,68,0)="explaining why you question the validity or amount of the debt.  To avoid"
^RC(343,19,1,69,0)="late charges, you must submit a dispute by the balance due date on the"
^RC(343,19,1,70,0)="statement. VA will not initiate collection if your dispute is received"
^RC(343,19,1,71,0)="within sixty (60) days from the initial billing statement.  If VA receives"
^RC(343,19,1,72,0)="your notice later than sixty (60) days and collection has been initiated,"
^RC(343,19,1,73,0)="it will continue while the dispute is being reviewed.  If the dispute is"
^RC(343,19,1,74,0)="resolved in your favor, all late charges will be removed from your"
^RC(343,19,1,75,0)="account, and any amounts withheld from your VA benefits, federal payments,"
^RC(343,19,1,76,0)="or wages will be refunded to you.  Refer to the ""Customer Service"" and"
^RC(343,19,1,77,0)="""Submitting Your Request"" sections below for more information."
^RC(343,19,1,78,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,79,0)="CUSTOMER SERVICE:  For additional information or assistance:"
^RC(343,19,1,80,0)="    In Person: At your local Veteran Affairs Medical Center's"
^RC(343,19,1,81,0)="               Agent Cashier's Office"
^RC(343,19,1,82,0)="    By Phone:  (see below for local information)"
^RC(343,19,1,83,0)="    Online:    Visit  www.domain.ext/vaforms to retrieve VA forms"
^RC(343,19,1,84,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,85,0)="SUBMITTING YOUR REQUEST:  Submit the required VA forms or documents to"
^RC(343,19,1,86,0)="apply for one of VA's Financial Hardship Programs:"
^RC(343,19,1,87,0)="    In Person: At your local Veteran Affairs Medical Center's Agent"
^RC(343,19,1,88,0)="               Cashier's Office"
^RC(343,19,1,89,0)="    By Mail:   Send completed forms and/or other required documentation"
^RC(343,19,1,90,0)="               to the VA address at the top right of your statement to the"
^RC(343,19,1,91,0)="               attention of the Fiscal Office/Bill of Collection Manager"
^RC(343,19,1,92,0)="For additional information, to request necessary forms or assistance in"
^RC(343,19,1,93,0)="accessing forms online, contact VA at 1-866-400-1238."
^RC(343,19,1,94,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,95,0)="REPRESENTATION:  An accredited representative of a Veteran Service"
^RC(343,19,1,96,0)="Organization or other service organization recognized by the Secretary of"
^RC(343,19,1,97,0)="Veterans Affairs may represent you without charge.  You may employ an"
^RC(343,19,1,98,0)="attorney or VA accredited agent to assist you.  The services of an"
^RC(343,19,1,99,0)="attorney or accredited agent representing you in adjudicative proceedings"
^RC(343,19,1,100,0)="before VA are subject to a fee limitation as set forth in 38 U.S.C. 5904."
^RC(343,19,1,101,0)="If you desire representation and have not already designated a"
^RC(343,19,1,102,0)="representative, contact VA at 1-866-400-1238 to request the necessary"
^RC(343,19,1,103,0)="forms.  If an attorney or accredited agent represents you before VA, a"
^RC(343,19,1,104,0)="copy of any agreement between you and the attorney or accredited agent"
^RC(343,19,1,105,0)="about the payment of the attorney's or agent's fees must be filed at the"
^RC(343,19,1,106,0)="following address:  Counsel to the Chairman (01C3), Board of Veterans "
^RC(343,19,1,107,0)="Appeals, 810 Vermont Avenue N.W., Washington D.C. 20420."
^RC(343,19,1,108,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,109,0)="NOTICE TO CUSTOMERS MAKING PAYMENT BY CHECK: When you provide a check as       "
^RC(343,19,1,110,0)="payment, you authorize VA to either use information from your check to"
^RC(343,19,1,111,0)="make a one-time electronic fund transfer from your account or to process"
^RC(343,19,1,112,0)="the payment as a check transaction.  When VA uses information from your"
^RC(343,19,1,113,0)="check to make an electronic fund transfer, funds may be withdrawn from "
^RC(343,19,1,114,0)="your account as soon as the day we process your payment, and you will not"
^RC(343,19,1,115,0)="receive your check back from the financial institution.  A Privacy Act"
^RC(343,19,1,116,0)="Statement required by 5 U.S.C. & 552a(e)(3) stating our authority for"
^RC(343,19,1,117,0)="soliciting and collecting the information from your check, and explaining"
^RC(343,19,1,118,0)="the purposes and routine uses which will be made of your check"
^RC(343,19,1,119,0)="information, VA Notice of Privacy Practices, IB 10-163 is available online"
^RC(343,19,1,120,0)="at www.domain.ext/vhapublications or call toll free at 1-866-400-1238 to"
^RC(343,19,1,121,0)="obtain a copy by mail.  Furnishing the check information is voluntary, but"
^RC(343,19,1,122,0)="a decision not to do so may require you to make payment by some other"
^RC(343,19,1,123,0)="method."
^RC(343,19,1,124,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,125,0)="QUESTIONS ABOUT PAYMENTS:  Payments made in the past ten (10) days may not"
^RC(343,19,1,126,0)="have been applied to your account by the time your statement was prepared."
^RC(343,19,1,127,0)="If so, this payment will be reflected in your account on the next"
^RC(343,19,1,128,0)="statement.  For assistance in understanding your statement and assessed"
^RC(343,19,1,129,0)="charges contact VA at (see below for local information)."
^RC(343,19,1,130,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
^RC(343,19,1,131,0)="VA PRIVACY:  The VA Notice of Privacy Practices, IB 10-163, which outlines"
^RC(343,19,1,132,0)="your privacy rights, is available online at www.domain.ext/vhapublications,"
^RC(343,19,1,133,0)="or you may obtain a copy by writing the VHA Privacy Office (10P2C1) at 810"
^RC(343,19,1,134,0)="Vermont Avenue NW, Washington, DC 20420."
^RC(343,19,1,135,0)="__________________________________________________________________________"
